     Andrew J. Pigors, being first duly sworn, deposes and states as follows:

I. PERSONAL INFORMATION AND QUALIFICATIONS TO TESTIFY

     1. My name is Andrew J. Pigors. I am over the age of 18 years and competent to testify as to the matters set forth in this Affidavit.

     2. I am the Plaintiff in this matter and the natural father of L.D.W., born in 2019 ("Lincoln" or "the child").

     3. I have personal knowledge of all facts set forth in this Affidavit, and if called as a witness, I could and would testify competently thereto under oath.

     4. I submit this Affidavit in support of my Motion to Modify Custody and to establish the factual basis for that Motion.

II. MY RELATIONSHIP WITH LINCOLN

A. From Birth Through 2024

     5. I have been an active, loving, and committed father to Lincoln since his birth in 2019.

     6. From Lincoln's birth through mid-2024, I maintained an informal shared parenting arrangement with the Defendant, Emily A. Watson ("Emily"). I exercised approximately 182.5 overnights per year with Lincoln, representing approximately 50% parenting time.

     7. During this time, I was deeply involved in all aspects of Lincoln's care and upbringing, including:

          a. Daily care activities: I fed Lincoln, bathed him, dressed him, and put him to bed. I changed diapers when he was an infant. I potty-trained him. I read to him every night before bed.

          b. Medical care: I attended doctor appointments. I took Lincoln to the doctor when he was sick. I administered medication as prescribed. I ensured he received all vaccinations.

          c. Developmental activities: I played with Lincoln. I taught him colors, numbers, and letters. I encouraged his curiosity and learning. I took him to the park, the library, and age-appropriate activities.

          d. Emotional support: I comforted Lincoln when he was upset or scared. I provided reassurance and security. I told him I loved him every day. I was there for him.

          e. Financial support: I provided financial support for Lincoln's needs, including food, clothing, diapers, toys, and other necessities.

     8. Lincoln and I developed a strong, healthy father-son bond. He looked to me for guidance, discipline, comfort, and love. When he was with me, he was happy, secure, and thriving.

     9. I maintained a stable, safe, and appropriate home environment for Lincoln. My home had everything Lincoln needed: his own bedroom, age-appropriate toys, books, safe outdoor play space, and a routine that provided stability and structure.

     10. During this period (2019-2024), there were no allegations of abuse, neglect, or safety concerns regarding my care of Lincoln. Emily never expressed concerns about Lincoln's safety with me during this time. We co-parented cooperatively for years.

     11. Our informal 50/50 arrangement worked well. Lincoln thrived with equal time with both parents. This is the arrangement I seek to restore through this Motion.

B. The Court's July 17, 2024 Order

     12. On July 17, 2024, this Court entered an Order Regarding Custody and Parenting Time that granted:
          • Joint legal custody to both Emily and me
          • Primary physical custody to Emily
          • Parenting time to me: 79 overnights per year

     13. This order reduced my parenting time from 182.5 overnights per year to 79 overnights per year—a reduction of 103.5 overnights (56.7% reduction).

     14. Despite this reduction, I accepted the Court's order and committed to exercising my court-ordered parenting time and maintaining my relationship with Lincoln.

     15. The July 17, 2024 order awarded joint legal custody to both parents, recognizing that both Emily and I are fit parents capable of making decisions regarding Lincoln's welfare.

C. Emily's Systematic Deprivation of My Relationship with Lincoln

     16. Since the July 17, 2024 order, Emily has systematically prevented me from exercising my parenting time with Lincoln.

     17. As of the date of this Affidavit (February 11, 2026), I have been deprived of 329+ days of parenting time with my son, including:

          • March 28 - May 5, 2024: 39 days (unilateral withholding by Emily)
          • October 20 - November 15, 2024: 26 days (unilateral withholding by Emily)
          • Various other dates: 72 days (refusals, cancellations, violations of schedule)
          • August 8, 2025 - February 11, 2026: 192+ days (ongoing ex parte suspension)

     18. During the period of August 8, 2025 through the present date (192+ consecutive days), I have had ZERO contact with Lincoln:

          • No parenting time
          • No phone calls
          • No video chats
          • No emails or messages
          • No cards or letters delivered to Lincoln
          • No information about Lincoln's wellbeing, health, or activities
          • Complete elimination of the father-son relationship

     19. I have been completely erased from my son's life for over six months.

     20. This deprivation has caused me profound emotional pain. I think about Lincoln every day. I worry about him. I miss him. I love him. I want to be his father. But Emily has taken that away from me.

     21. More importantly, this deprivation has caused Lincoln profound harm. A five-year-old child needs his father. Lincoln has been deprived of his father's love, guidance, and presence for 329+ days—nearly a full year. This is child abuse by another name.

III. EMILY'S FALSE ALLEGATIONS

     22. Emily's systematic deprivation of my relationship with Lincoln has been accomplished through a calculated campaign of false allegations.

     23. I will address each of Emily's false allegations and explain why they are false:

A. False Allegation: Poisoning

     24. Emily has alleged that I poisoned Lincoln or gave him substances that made him ill.

     25. This allegation is completely false.

     26. I have NEVER poisoned Lincoln. I have NEVER given him any harmful substances. I have NEVER done anything that would harm him.

     27. When Lincoln was in my care, I fed him age-appropriate, healthy food. I ensured he was safe and well-cared-for. I would never harm my son.

     28. Emily's poisoning allegation has been investigated and disproven:

          a. Medical records show no evidence of poisoning
          b. No toxicology findings
          c. No hospital admissions for poisoning
          d. No physician findings of poisoning
          e. Police investigated and found no basis for the allegation

     29. Emily made this allegation to justify denying me parenting time. It is a lie.

B. False Allegation: Assault

     30. Emily has alleged that I assaulted her or Lincoln.

     31. This allegation is completely false.

     32. I have NEVER assaulted Emily. I have NEVER assaulted Lincoln. I have NEVER been physically violent toward anyone.

     33. Police investigated Emily's assault allegations and found no evidence:

          a. No criminal charges were filed
          b. No evidence of assault was found
          c. No injuries were documented
          d. No hospital treatment for injuries occurred

     34. I am not a violent person. I have no history of violence. I have no criminal record. This allegation is a fabrication designed to eliminate me from Lincoln's life.

C. False Allegation: Suicidality and Mental Instability (Two Incidents)

     35. On two separate occasions (October 2023 and June 2024), Emily alleged that I was suicidal and mentally unstable.

     36. Both allegations are completely false.

     37. I was NOT suicidal on either occasion. I have NEVER been suicidal. I have NEVER had suicidal thoughts. I value my life and want to live to see Lincoln grow up.

     38. I am NOT mentally unstable. I am a stable, healthy, functioning adult with appropriate mental health.

     39. On both occasions, police responded to Emily's allegations and conducted welfare checks:

          a. October 2023: Police found me stable and appropriate. No mental health hold. No hospitalization. No danger found.
          
          b. June 2024: Police found me stable and appropriate. No mental health hold. No hospitalization. No danger found.

     40. Medical evaluations on both occasions found:

          a. No suicidal ideation
          b. No mental health diagnosis
          c. No need for psychiatric treatment
          d. No danger to self or others

     41. I have never been diagnosed with any mental health condition. I have never been prescribed psychiatric medication. I have never been hospitalized for mental health treatment.

     42. Emily made these false allegations to create a paper trail suggesting I am dangerous or unstable. The goal was to justify denying me parenting time. The allegations are lies.

D. False Allegation: Threat and Danger (PPO)

     43. On November 17, 2023, Emily obtained a Personal Protection Order (PPO) against me in Case No. 2023-5907-PP.

     44. In her PPO petition, Emily alleged that I threatened her and posed a danger to her and Lincoln.

     45. These allegations are completely false.

     46. I have NEVER threatened Emily. I have NEVER made any statement that could reasonably be interpreted as a threat. I have NEVER engaged in behavior that poses any danger to Emily or Lincoln.

     47. The PPO was obtained through misrepresentation and false allegations. The evidence demonstrates this:

          a. No police charges were ever filed against me for threat or danger
          b. No criminal investigation was initiated
          c. This Court awarded me equal legal custody on July 17, 2024—which would be unconscionable if I posed a danger to Emily or Lincoln
          d. The HealthWest evaluation found no concerns regarding threat or danger

     48. If I actually posed a threat or danger:

          a. Police would have filed criminal charges
          b. A criminal investigation would be ongoing
          c. Child Protective Services would have removed Lincoln from my care
          d. This Court would not have awarded me equal legal custody
          e. The HealthWest evaluator would have documented concerns

     49. None of this occurred because I pose no threat and no danger. The PPO was fraudulent.

     50. Emily obtained the fraudulent PPO to gain a tactical advantage in custody litigation and to justify denying me parenting time.

E. False Allegations: Emergency Requiring Suspension (5+ Incidents)

     51. Beginning August 8, 2025, Emily filed a series of emergency motions seeking ex parte suspension of my parenting time, alleging that emergencies existed requiring immediate suspension.

     52. These emergency allegations are false. No emergency existed on August 8, 2025. No emergency has existed at any time since then.

     53. The proof that no emergency exists:

          a. No police involvement in any alleged "emergency"
          b. No 911 calls
          c. No criminal investigation
          d. No criminal charges
          e. No Child Protective Services involvement
          f. No hospital admissions
          g. No documented injuries to Lincoln
          h. No medical findings of harm

     54. If a true emergency existed involving danger to Lincoln, Emily would have:

          a. Called 911
          b. Taken Lincoln to the emergency room
          c. Reported the matter to police
          d. Reported the matter to Child Protective Services
          e. Obtained emergency protective custody through CPS

     55. Emily did none of these things because no emergency exists.

     56. Instead, Emily filed ex parte motions with the Court, seeking suspension orders based on unverified allegations. These orders were granted without a hearing, without my opportunity to respond, and without any evidentiary showing.

     57. The ex parte suspension orders have now been in place for 192+ consecutive days, depriving Lincoln of his father for over six months based on false allegations of "emergency."

     58. This is not an emergency. This is a weaponization of the court system to eliminate me from Lincoln's life.

F. Summary: 100% False Allegation Rate

     59. Every allegation Emily has made against me has been false:

          • Poisoning: FALSE (medical records, police reports)
          • Assault: FALSE (police reports, no charges)
          • Suicidality (Incident 1): FALSE (police welfare check, medical evaluation)
          • Suicidality (Incident 2): FALSE (police welfare check, medical evaluation)
          • Threat/Danger (PPO): FALSE (no charges, court awarded equal legal custody, HealthWest found no concerns)
          • Emergency 1 (8/8/25): FALSE (no police, no CPS, no hospital)
          • Emergency 2 (9/4/25): FALSE (no police, no CPS, no hospital)
          • Emergency 3 (10/29/25): FALSE (no police, no CPS, no hospital)
          • Emergency 4 (11/26/25): FALSE (no police, no CPS, no hospital)
          • Emergency 5 (12/17/25): FALSE (no police, no CPS, no hospital)

     60. Every single allegation has been investigated and disproven. Yet Emily continues to make new allegations, and the deprivation continues.

IV. THE HEALTHWEST EVALUATION

     61. In 2024, I participated in a comprehensive psychological evaluation conducted by HealthWest, a professional mental health organization.

     62. The evaluation included:

          a. Multiple clinical interviews with me
          b. Psychological testing (including standardized instruments)
          c. Review of medical records and other documents
          d. Assessment of my parenting capacity
          e. Assessment of my mental health
          f. Assessment of child safety

     63. I cooperated fully with the evaluation. I answered all questions honestly. I completed all testing. I provided all requested information.

     64. The HealthWest evaluation reached the following findings regarding me:

          ✓ I am an appropriate caregiver
          ✓ I have appropriate parenting capacity
          ✓ I present no mental health concerns
          ✓ I present no safety concerns
          ✓ I am psychologically stable
          ✓ I am not suicidal
          ✓ I am not dangerous
          ✓ I pose no threat to Lincoln
          ✓ I have a positive bond with Lincoln
          ✓ I am capable of meeting Lincoln's needs

     65. The HealthWest evaluation completely disproves Emily's allegations against me. A professional, independent, comprehensive clinical assessment found that all of Emily's allegations are baseless.

     66. The HealthWest evaluation also found concerning behaviors by Emily:

          ⚠ Emily engages in gatekeeping behaviors
          ⚠ Emily has systematically interfered with my relationship with Lincoln
          ⚠ Emily has engaged in parental alienation
          ⚠ Emily's allegations against me lack foundation
          ⚠ Emily prioritizes her conflict with me over Lincoln's needs

     67. HealthWest recommended:

          → Restore my parenting time
          → Expand my parenting time beyond the current order
          → Order Emily to cease gatekeeping behaviors
          → Consider therapy for Emily regarding co-parenting
          → Consider reunification therapy for Lincoln and me (to repair damage from 329+ days deprivation)

     68. The HealthWest evaluation is the most important evidence in this case. It is professional, comprehensive, independent, unbiased, and based on clinical assessment. It completely vindicates me and exposes Emily's false allegations.

V. MY FITNESS AS A PARENT

     69. I am a fit, appropriate, and loving father. The evidence demonstrates this:

A. I Have No Criminal Record

     70. I have no criminal convictions. I have no pending criminal charges. I have never been arrested. I have a clean record.

B. I Have No History of Abuse or Neglect

     71. I have no history of child abuse or neglect. There have been no founded Child Protective Services reports against me. Lincoln has never been removed from my care. No abuse or neglect has ever occurred.

C. I Have Stable Employment and Housing

     72. I maintain stable employment. I have a steady income that allows me to support Lincoln financially.

     73. I maintain a stable, appropriate home that is safe and suitable for Lincoln. My home has:

          • Lincoln's own bedroom with a bed, dresser, toys, and books
          • Safe, clean living space
          • Age-appropriate outdoor play area
          • Adequate food in the refrigerator and pantry
          • Working utilities (heat, water, electricity)
          • No safety hazards

     74. My home has been inspected by professionals (as part of the HealthWest evaluation) and found to be appropriate for Lincoln.

D. I Have No Substance Abuse Issues

     75. I do not abuse alcohol or drugs. I do not have a substance abuse problem. I have never been in treatment for substance abuse. I do not use illegal drugs.

E. I Have Appropriate Mental and Physical Health

     76. As documented by the HealthWest evaluation, I have appropriate mental health. I am psychologically stable. I have no mental health diagnosis. I am not on psychiatric medication.

     77. I am in good physical health. I am physically capable of caring for Lincoln.

F. I Am Willing and Able to Co-Parent

     78. I am willing to co-parent cooperatively with Emily. I have never interfered with Emily's parenting time. I have never made false allegations against Emily. I have never sought to eliminate Emily from Lincoln's life.

     79. I want Lincoln to have a relationship with both of his parents. I recognize that Emily is Lincoln's mother and that Lincoln loves her. I would never seek to damage that relationship.

     80. I am committed to facilitating Lincoln's relationship with Emily, even though Emily has refused to reciprocate.

G. I Comply with Court Orders

     81. I have complied with all court orders in this case. I have never violated a court order. I have never violated Emily's parenting time. I have never engaged in self-help or contemptuous behavior.

     82. When I was permitted parenting time (before the August 8, 2025 suspension), I exercised that time appropriately. I returned Lincoln to Emily on time. I followed the parenting time schedule. I communicated appropriately about Lincoln's care.

H. I Have Appropriate Parenting Skills

     83. I have demonstrated appropriate parenting skills for five years. During the 50/50 arrangement that existed from 2019-2024, Lincoln thrived in my care. He was happy, healthy, safe, and developing appropriately.

     84. The HealthWest evaluation confirms that I have appropriate parenting capacity and skills.

VI. EMILY'S UNFITNESS TO HAVE PRIMARY CUSTODY

     85. While I would prefer joint physical custody with equal parenting time, Emily's conduct demonstrates that she is unfit to maintain primary custody.

A. Emily Has Systematically Violated Court Orders (329+ Days)

     86. Emily has willfully and systematically violated court-ordered parenting time, depriving me of 329+ days of contact with Lincoln.

     87. This includes:

          • 39 days of unilateral withholding (March 28 - May 5, 2024)
          • 26 days of withholding (October 20 - November 15, 2024)
          • 72 days of various violations (refusals, cancellations, schedule violations)
          • 192+ days of deprivation achieved through abuse of ex parte procedures

     88. A parent who willfully violates court orders for 329+ days has demonstrated contempt for the legal system and unfitness to maintain primary custody.

B. Emily Has Engaged in Systematic Parental Alienation

     89. Emily has engaged in a systematic campaign to alienate Lincoln from me. This includes:

          a. Making false allegations designed to portray me as dangerous, unstable, or harmful
          b. Depriving Lincoln of 329+ days of contact with me
          c. Speaking negatively about me to Lincoln (likely, based on alienation patterns documented by HealthWest)
          d. Using the legal system to eliminate me from Lincoln's life
          e. Prioritizing her conflict with me over Lincoln's need for both parents

     90. Parental alienation is a form of child abuse. A parent who engages in alienation is unfit to maintain primary custody.

C. Emily Has Made Systematic False Allegations

     91. Emily has made at least 11 major false allegations against me over a 22-month period. All have been disproven.

     92. A parent who systematically makes false allegations to police, medical providers, and courts demonstrates:

          • Lack of moral fitness
          • Willingness to lie under oath
          • Willingness to abuse legal processes
          • Willingness to harm the child's relationship with the other parent for litigation advantage
          • Unfitness to maintain primary custody

D. Emily Has Obtained a Fraudulent PPO

     93. Emily obtained a Personal Protection Order through demonstrably false allegations. This fraudulent PPO has been used to:

          • Interfere with my parenting time
          • Damage my reputation
          • Justify ex parte suspension orders
          • Manipulate custody outcomes

     94. Obtaining a fraudulent restraining order through perjury demonstrates moral unfitness and disqualifies Emily from maintaining primary custody.

E. Emily Prioritizes Conflict Over Lincoln's Needs

     95. Throughout this litigation, Emily has demonstrated that she prioritizes her conflict with me over Lincoln's needs.

     96. Lincoln needs his father. Lincoln has a right to a relationship with both parents. Emily has systematically deprived Lincoln of this relationship for 329+ days.

     97. A parent who deprives a child of a relationship with the other parent—without any legitimate safety basis—is prioritizing adult conflict over the child's wellbeing. This demonstrates unfitness.

F. Emily Violates MCL 722.27a

     98. Michigan law (MCL 722.27a) establishes a strong presumption that parenting time is in the child's best interests unless clear and convincing evidence shows it would endanger the child.

     99. Emily has provided no such clear and convincing evidence. All of her allegations have been disproven.

     100. Yet Emily has systematically interfered with my parenting time for 329+ days, in direct violation of MCL 722.27a.

     101. A parent who violates the statutory presumption favoring parenting time is unfit to maintain primary custody.

VII. WHY JOINT PHYSICAL CUSTODY WITH EQUAL PARENTING TIME IS IN LINCOLN'S BEST INTERESTS

     102. I seek modification of custody to establish joint physical custody with equal parenting time (182.5 overnights per year each).

     103. This arrangement is in Lincoln's best interests for the following reasons:

A. It Restores the Arrangement That Worked (2019-2024)

     104. From Lincoln's birth through mid-2024, Lincoln thrived under a 50/50 shared parenting arrangement. He spent approximately equal time with both parents. He was happy, healthy, and developing appropriately.

     105. That arrangement worked. It should be restored.

B. It Maximizes Lincoln's Time with Both Parents

     106. Lincoln loves both of his parents. Lincoln needs both of his parents. Equal parenting time ensures that Lincoln maintains strong relationships with both Emily and me.

C. It Complies with MCL 722.27a

     107. Equal parenting time is consistent with Michigan's strong statutory presumption favoring maximum parenting time.

D. It Is Supported by the HealthWest Evaluation

     108. The HealthWest evaluation recommends restoration and expansion of my parenting time. Equal parenting time implements that recommendation.

E. It Addresses the Harm from 329+ Days of Deprivation

     109. Lincoln has been deprived of his father for 329+ days. This has caused profound harm to the father-son relationship and to Lincoln's emotional wellbeing.

     110. Equal parenting time is necessary to repair this harm and restore the relationship.

F. It Prevents Future Gatekeeping

     111. Under the current arrangement (primary custody to Emily), Emily has demonstrated that she will engage in systematic gatekeeping and deprivation.

     112. Equal parenting time removes Emily's ability to gatekeep. If time is equal, there is no gatekeeper.

G. It Serves Lincoln's Developmental Needs

     113. Lincoln is five years old. At this age, children need both mothers and fathers. Research in developmental psychology demonstrates that father involvement is critical for healthy child development.

     114. Lincoln needs his father. Equal parenting time ensures that need is met.

VIII. ALTERNATIVELY, I SHOULD BE PRIMARY PHYSICAL CUSTODIAN

     115. If the Court declines to order equal parenting time, I respectfully request that I be designated the primary physical custodian with Emily receiving reasonable parenting time.

     116. This alternative is justified by:

          a. Emily's 329+ days of parenting time violations
          b. Emily's systematic false allegations
          c. Emily's moral unfitness (false allegations, fraudulent PPO, perjury)
          d. Emily's absolute unwillingness to facilitate my relationship with Lincoln
          e. The need to protect Lincoln from further alienation

     117. Designating me as primary custodian would:

          a. Protect Lincoln from further alienation
          b. Ensure compliance with parenting time orders (I have never violated Emily's time)
          c. Remove Emily's ability to weaponize custody
          d. Hold Emily accountable for her violations
          e. Provide Lincoln with a stable environment with the parent who will facilitate relationships with both parents

     118. Under this alternative, Emily would receive reasonable parenting time, which I commit to facilitating. I would never engage in the gatekeeping and alienation that Emily has engaged in.

IX. I AM ENTITLED TO 329 DAYS OF MAKEUP PARENTING TIME

     119. I have been wrongfully deprived of 329+ days of parenting time with Lincoln.

     120. Michigan law (MCL 722.27a(3)) requires that makeup parenting time be awarded when parenting time has been wrongfully denied.

     121. I request 329 days of makeup parenting time, to be scheduled at my discretion over the next 18 months, in blocks of no less than 3 consecutive days each.

     122. This makeup time is essential to repair the father-son relationship that has been damaged by 329+ days of deprivation.

X. IMPACT OF DEPRIVATION ON ME

     123. The 329+ days of deprivation have caused me profound emotional harm:

          a. I think about Lincoln every day. I miss him desperately.
          b. I worry about him constantly. Is he safe? Is he happy? Does he remember me?
          c. I have been unable to be his father—to provide guidance, comfort, love, discipline, and support.
          d. I have missed birthdays, holidays, and daily moments that I can never get back.
          e. I have suffered depression, anxiety, and grief from the loss of my relationship with my son.

     124. No parent should have to endure what I have endured—being erased from their child's life based on false allegations.

XI. IMPACT OF DEPRIVATION ON LINCOLN

     125. More importantly, the 329+ days of deprivation have caused Lincoln profound harm:

          a. Lincoln has been deprived of his father's love, guidance, and presence for nearly a year.
          b. Lincoln has been deprived of the father-son bond that we had built over five years.
          c. Lincoln is being raised to believe false things about his father (that I am dangerous, unstable, or harmful).
          d. Lincoln is being taught by Emily's example that it is acceptable to lie, violate court orders, and manipulate the legal system.
          e. Lincoln is being denied his fundamental right to a relationship with both parents.

     126. This is child abuse. It may not leave physical scars, but the emotional and psychological damage is profound and lasting.

     127. Lincoln needs his father. I am here. I am ready. I am willing. I am able. I am fit. I want to be Lincoln's father.

     128. Emily has stolen nearly a year of my son's childhood from me. She has stolen nearly a year of his father's presence from Lincoln.

     129. This must stop. Now.

XII. PRAYER FOR RELIEF

     130. For all of the reasons set forth in this Affidavit and in the Motion and Brief in Support, I respectfully request that this Court:

          A. Find that proper cause exists to modify custody;
          B. Find that a change of circumstances exists warranting modification;
          C. Conduct a best interests analysis under MCL 722.23;
          D. Find that the best interests of Lincoln favor modification;
          E. Modify custody to establish joint physical custody with equal parenting time (182.5 overnights each per year);
          F. Alternatively, designate me as the primary physical custodian with Emily receiving reasonable parenting time;
          G. Award me 329 days of makeup parenting time;
          H. Order Emily to comply with MCL 722.27a and facilitate parenting time;
          I. Award attorney fees and costs to me;
          J. Grant such other and further relief as the Court deems just and equitable.

XIII. VERIFICATION

     131. I have read the foregoing Affidavit and the statements contained herein are true to the best of my knowledge, information, and belief.

     132. I declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the State of Michigan that the foregoing is true and correct.

